Dialogue: 0,00:01:41.98,00:01:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, watch out. Watch out.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:48.86,00:01:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:50.15,00:01:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Great to see you.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:51.40,00:01:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, glad you made it.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:53.86,00:01:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This can't be Ajit. \NHe's a little man already.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:56.87,00:01:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,- Unbelievable. \N- I hope you're hungry, Adrian.
Dialogue: 0,00:01:59.37,00:02:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm famished. How are you, Aparna?
Dialogue: 0,00:02:01.83,00:02:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- I made that fish curry you love. \N- I can't wait.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:05.33,00:02:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,She gets more beautiful \Nevery time I see her. Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,00:02:08.17,00:02:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Strange, isn't it? \NBut her fish curry is still awful.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:13.76,00:02:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You were mysterious on the phone. \NWhy didn't you attend the conference?
Dialogue: 0,00:02:16.64,00:02:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,- I will show you, Adrian, sir. \N- Satnam, stop "siring" me.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:27.44,00:02:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How deep do we need to go?
Dialogue: 0,00:02:29.40,00:02:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Eleven thousand feet.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:31.65,00:02:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I searched all over India \Nfor this thing.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:34.70,00:02:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Used to be the deepest copper mine \Nin the world.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:42.04,00:02:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember my brother, Gurdeep? \NHe's a student now.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:44.54,00:02:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Namaste, Dr. Helmsley, sir.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:46.58,00:02:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Adrian. It's just Adrian.
Dialogue: 0,00:02:51.55,00:02:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Just don't pour too much, huh?
Dialogue: 0,00:02:55.76,00:02:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you work in this heat?
Dialogue: 0,00:02:58.22,00:02:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You've come on a good day, \Nmy friend.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:00.10,00:03:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes it can hit 120 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:03.72,00:03:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to come and meet \NDr. Lokesh...
Dialogue: 0,00:03:05.68,00:03:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,...a Fellow of quantum physics \Nat the university in Chennai.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:08.65,00:03:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Helmsley.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:12.61,00:03:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what are we looking at?
Dialogue: 0,00:03:15.19,00:03:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,These are neutrinos acting normally.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:17.07,00:03:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Minuscule mass, \Nno electrical charge.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:20.24,00:03:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They pass through ordinary matter \Nalmost undisturbed.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:22.91,00:03:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Your message said the count doubled \Nafter the last solar eruptions.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:26.16,00:03:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That was last week.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:29.12,00:03:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But this happened two days ago.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:35.88,00:03:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The biggest Sun eruptions \Nin human history...
Dialogue: 0,00:03:39.38,00:03:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,...causing the highest neutrino count \Nwe've ever recorded.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:43.31,00:03:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,My God.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:48.19,00:03:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not what worries me, Adrian.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:51.27,00:03:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,For the first time ever...
Dialogue: 0,00:03:54.52,00:03:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,...the neutrinos are causing \Na physical reaction.
Dialogue: 0,00:03:59.49,00:04:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:05.91,00:04:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That feels very good.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:09.41,00:04:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, follow me.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:15.75,00:04:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't believe this.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:19.42,00:04:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This water tank goes down \Nanother 6000 feet.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:24.01,00:04:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like the neutrinos \Ncoming from the Sun...
Dialogue: 0,00:04:26.60,00:04:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,...have mutated into a new kind \Nof nuclear particle.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:37.28,00:04:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They're heating up \Nthe Earth's core...
Dialogue: 0,00:04:40.28,00:04:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,...and suddenly act like microwaves.
Dialogue: 0,00:04:55.38,00:04:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen, \Nas promised, no speech...
Dialogue: 0,00:04:59.67,00:05:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,...just a thank-you...
Dialogue: 0,00:05:02.01,00:05:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,...because tonight, \Nwith your extraordinary generosity...
Dialogue: 0,00:05:04.93,00:05:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,...we have raised $1.7 million.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:09.47,00:05:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a stiff drink, \Nbecause I'm locking the doors...
Dialogue: 0,00:05:12.19,00:05:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,- ... and passing the hat around again. \N- It's okay. It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:15.44,00:05:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,- I work for the White House. \N- I don't care.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:17.61,00:05:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a black-tie event.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:20.19,00:05:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Scotty.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:21.74,00:05:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. Adrian, I thought you were \Nin India. What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,00:05:25.53,00:05:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,- I need yourjacket. \N- What?
Dialogue: 0,00:05:27.33,00:05:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I gotta speak to Anheuser. \NGive me your damn jacket, please.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:30.41,00:05:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- All right. \N- Okay?
Dialogue: 0,00:05:31.91,00:05:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,- All right, here. Here. \N- Hold that for a minute, will you?
Dialogue: 0,00:05:37.88,00:05:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Easy, that's a $600 jacket.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:41.34,00:05:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Anheuser?
Dialogue: 0,00:05:43.30,00:05:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Anheuser.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:45.72,00:05:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:50.72,00:05:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- Do I know you? \N- Sorry, sir.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:52.14,00:05:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,My name's Dr. Adrian Helmsley.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:53.69,00:05:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a deputy geologist at the Office \Nof Science and Technology Policy.
Dialogue: 0,00:05:58.40,00:06:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, fellas.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:00.40,00:06:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that this is a fundraiser, \Nnot a frat party, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:06:04.49,00:06:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's important, sir. \N- You know what? It always is.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:07.07,00:06:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Make an appointment with my... \NYou know, even better:
Dialogue: 0,00:06:09.74,00:06:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Have your boss bring it up \Nat the quarterly briefing.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:12.45,00:06:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a good plan.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:14.62,00:06:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I just traveled 20 straight hours \Nto get here, sir.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:17.13,00:06:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't slept in two days.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:19.04,00:06:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to read this, sir. \NYou need to read it now.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:27.76,00:06:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me guess, \Nnational geology crisis?
Dialogue: 0,00:06:32.18,00:06:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:51.49,00:06:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- Who do you report to? \N- Lee Cavazos.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:54.41,00:06:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Not anymore.
Dialogue: 0,00:06:58.75,00:07:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Alan, bring the car around.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:01.59,00:07:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- You're gonna wish you took a shower. \N- Sir?
Dialogue: 0,00:07:03.84,00:07:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You're about to meet the president.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:05.72,00:07:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,00:07:07.13,00:07:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Get that to the office.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:25.49,00:07:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:26.99,00:07:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to meet privately \Nwith my fellow heads of state.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:33.16,00:07:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Makarenko wishes \Nto have his interpreters present.
Dialogue: 0,00:07:35.08,00:07:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. President, I can assure you...
Dialogue: 0,00:07:39.37,00:07:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,...your English is more than sufficient \Nfor what I have to say.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:02.77,00:08:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Presidents.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:09.03,00:08:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Six months ago...
Dialogue: 0,00:08:11.32,00:08:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,...I was made aware of a situation \Nso devastating...
Dialogue: 0,00:08:15.54,00:08:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,...that, at first, I refused to believe it.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:19.83,00:08:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,00:08:21.71,00:08:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,...through the concerted efforts...
Dialogue: 0,00:08:24.46,00:08:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,...of our brightest scientists...
Dialogue: 0,00:08:27.17,00:08:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,...we have confirmed its validity.
Dialogue: 0,00:08:32.93,00:08:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The world as we know it...
Dialogue: 0,00:08:38.39,00:08:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,...will soon come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,00:09:58.93,00:10:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Has His Highness had an opportunity \Nto study the dossier?
Dialogue: 0,00:10:07.23,00:10:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You must understand, \NI have a very big family, Mr...?
Dialogue: 0,00:10:11.82,00:10:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaacs.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:13.70,00:10:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,One billion dollars is a lot of money.
Dialogue: 0,00:10:17.16,00:10:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid the amount is in euros, \NYour Highness.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:42.24,00:11:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This mass suicide was actually \Ndiscovered by a documentary crew...
Dialogue: 0,00:11:45.83,00:11:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,...here in the ancient Mayan city \Nof Tikal.
Dialogue: 0,00:11:48.29,00:11:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the victims, \Nand we've seen many...
Dialogue: 0,00:11:50.46,00:11:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,...are said to have adhered \Nto the Mayan-Quiche calendar...
Dialogue: 0,00:11:53.34,00:11:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,...which predicts \Nthe end of time to occur...
Dialogue: 0,00:11:55.59,00:11:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,...on the 21st of December \Nof this year...
Dialogue: 0,00:11:57.97,00:12:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,...due to the Sun's \Ndestructive forces.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:00.18,00:12:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Mark.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:01.43,00:12:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Strangely enough, \Nscientific records do support the fact...
Dialogue: 0,00:12:05.81,00:12:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,...that we are heading for the biggest \Nsolar climax in recorded history.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:13.73,00:12:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, yes.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:14.94,00:12:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Apparently many people believe \Nthat the Mayan calendar predicts...
Dialogue: 0,00:12:18.95,00:12:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,...that there's supposed \Nto be a galactic alignment...
Dialogue: 0,00:12:21.66,00:12:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a dead man.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:22.87,00:12:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a dead man. I'm a dead man.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:25.87,00:12:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,...it's the end of the world in 2012.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:29.33,00:12:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Goddamn it.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:35.80,00:12:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Kate. I'm practically \Non the freeway right now.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:39.42,00:12:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm hurtling toward you \Nas we speak.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:43.18,00:12:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you relax? \NYeah, I'll be there any second.
Dialogue: 0,00:12:47.14,00:12:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You know it's a vacation \Nand not a doctor's appointment, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:12:50.48,00:12:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That it's supposed to be fun?
Dialogue: 0,00:12:52.15,00:12:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember fun, don't you, Kate?
Dialogue: 0,00:12:54.31,00:12:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember where you were \Nwhen it stopped being fun for you?
Dialogue: 0,00:12:59.40,00:13:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I got it.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:06.20,00:13:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Bug spray? Oh, yeah, because \Nit's mosquito season in Yellowstone.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:10.12,00:13:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a whole bunch. Okay, I gotta go, \Nbecause I'm in a bad-reception area.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:21.47,00:13:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, man.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:22.68,00:13:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you look at that?
Dialogue: 0,00:13:24.68,00:13:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Sick.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:31.98,00:13:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Merrill, I told you.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:33.77,00:13:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to move back \Nto Wisconsin.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:36.77,00:13:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but these little mini-quakes \Nare really getting on my nerves.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:40.28,00:13:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,A little surface crack? You're not \Ngonna be inconvenienced by that.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:43.53,00:13:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, surface cracks. \NI got a plastic surgeon for that.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:46.32,00:13:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank God for those shake-proof \Ncoffee mugs, Lisa.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:48.79,00:13:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,They show the true nature \Nof us Californians.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:51.04,00:13:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll not bow to these inconvenient \Nthings like surface cracks.
Dialogue: 0,00:13:55.42,00:13:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have a funny mini-quake story \Nand wanna share it, call 555-1070...
Dialogue: 0,00:14:08.10,00:14:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hi, Daddy. \N- Hi, baby.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:09.89,00:14:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- How are you, sweetie? \N- Good.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:12.23,00:14:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Jackson, what is this?
Dialogue: 0,00:14:14.31,00:14:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't call me that. \NI'm your dad.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:17.36,00:14:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:18.57,00:14:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You're taking them camping \Nin a limo?
Dialogue: 0,00:14:21.44,00:14:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, great.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:22.90,00:14:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened to your temp job?
Dialogue: 0,00:14:24.70,00:14:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you know, better hours, \Nmore time to write.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:27.70,00:14:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What about sleeping? Have you \Nbeen doing any of that lately?
Dialogue: 0,00:14:30.62,00:14:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I've said it a thousand times, no lipo \Non Fridays. It's too messy. Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:35.92,00:14:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- Morning, Jackson. \N- Hi.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:37.42,00:14:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,- Nice ride. \N- Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:38.75,00:14:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Guys, have a nice trip.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:40.25,00:14:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, watch out for the bears. \NYou know, they're:
Dialogue: 0,00:14:43.05,00:14:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye, Gordon.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:44.47,00:14:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- Love you, honey. \N- Bye.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:46.59,00:14:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- Okay, so, Lil... Oh, yeah. \N- You tell him.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:49.47,00:14:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me what?
Dialogue: 0,00:14:50.68,00:14:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,She needs to put these on \Nbefore she goes to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:53.18,00:14:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- I love you. \N- Love you, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,00:14:54.48,00:14:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hey. \N- You okay?
Dialogue: 0,00:15:00.11,00:15:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They've been looking forward \Nto spending time with you.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:02.28,00:15:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:03.53,00:15:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,- So don't be on your computer. \N- Got it.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:10.28,00:15:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Love you.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:15.08,00:15:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- So this time, we hit Japan. \N- So?
Dialogue: 0,00:15:19.38,00:15:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you could visit your boy, Will.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:21.25,00:15:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Afternoon, ladies.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:22.75,00:15:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hello there. \N- Hello, handsome.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:24.42,00:15:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you even listening to me?
Dialogue: 0,00:15:25.97,00:15:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, I am, Harry.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:27.72,00:15:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard from Audrey \Nyou're a grandpa now.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:29.76,00:15:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you mind keeping your nose \Nout of my family?
Dialogue: 0,00:15:32.39,00:15:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You're cramping my style, baby. \NThere we are.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:35.48,00:15:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So he married a Japanese girl. \NHow is that the end of the world?
Dialogue: 0,00:15:39.10,00:15:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Tony. \NYou should at least go see him.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:41.40,00:15:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- You see your boy? \N- Not as much as I'd like.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:44.28,00:15:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,D.C. is a long way, \Nbut at least we talk.
Dialogue: 0,00:15:46.82,00:15:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,About what?
Dialogue: 0,00:15:48.32,00:15:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Life, and how short it is.
Dialogue: 0,00:16:14.89,00:16:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell was that?
Dialogue: 0,00:17:19.29,00:17:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Break it down.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:25.21,00:17:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- I liked that song. \N- We lost it.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:27.00,00:17:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,...going on the West Coast \Nwith all those surface cracks.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:30.97,00:17:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I told myself, "Charlie, \Nget your stupid ass to Yellowstone. "
Dialogue: 0,00:17:35.51,00:17:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to miss all the fun \Nwhen it finally blows.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:39.35,00:17:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me tell you, \Nthere's been government people...
Dialogue: 0,00:17:41.81,00:17:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,...flying in and out all morning, \Nand trust me, they did not look happy.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:47.27,00:17:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- Always remember folks: \N- That's weird.
Dialogue: 0,00:17:49.78,00:17:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,- You heard it first from Charlie. \N- Yeah, just when he said that?
Dialogue: 0,00:17:53.45,00:17:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the odds?
Dialogue: 0,00:17:55.70,00:17:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not seeing soil liquefaction \Nwe'd expect...
Dialogue: 0,00:17:58.12,00:18:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,...or any evidence of fracture \Npropagation within the tectonic plates.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:01.58,00:18:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- In English. \N- The activity on the coast...
Dialogue: 0,00:18:03.79,00:18:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,...is not caused by tecto... \NBy regular earthquakes.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:06.42,00:18:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And these surface cracks have \Nnothing to do with shifting fault lines.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:09.96,00:18:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You suggesting this could be the \Nbeginning of the Cho Ming operation?
Dialogue: 0,00:18:13.34,00:18:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Helmsley is flying to Yellowstone \Nthis morning to collect more data.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:16.84,00:18:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We have been following the schedule \Nyou established, Mr. Helmsley.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:21.06,00:18:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The most important schedule \Nin the history of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:23.73,00:18:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you're telling me \Nwe have to throw it out?
Dialogue: 0,00:18:26.56,00:18:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:29.52,00:18:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:34.70,00:18:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know how many times \NI've heard those words in this office?
Dialogue: 0,00:18:38.78,00:18:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Zero.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:41.83,00:18:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy, where are we going?
Dialogue: 0,00:18:44.16,00:18:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Going to this really special place \Nthat I know.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:47.33,00:18:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a place where your mom and I \Nused to hang out a lot.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:50.34,00:18:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't wanna know \Nwhere you and Mom had sex.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:52.84,00:18:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm not ready for that, Jackson. \N- Stop calling me that.
Dialogue: 0,00:18:55.55,00:18:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's creeping me out. \NWhat's wrong with "Dad"?
Dialogue: 0,00:18:58.89,00:19:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,- Grumpy Grumperson. \N- Daddy, look at this.
Dialogue: 0,00:19:02.18,00:19:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That wasn't here before.
Dialogue: 0,00:19:04.77,00:19:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we do?
Dialogue: 0,00:19:06.69,00:19:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Go get your hat.
Dialogue: 0,00:19:13.19,00:19:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you see the signs?
Dialogue: 0,00:19:23.12,00:19:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Used to be a lake here.
Dialogue: 0,00:19:25.20,00:19:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't look much of a lake to me.
Dialogue: 0,00:19:27.67,00:19:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, \Nthe whole damn thing's gone.
Dialogue: 0,00:19:31.67,00:19:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,- Come on, let's check it out. \N- Grwat.
Dialogue: 0,00:19:56.57,00:19:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Subjects have now entered \Nhot zone.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:12.54,00:20:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,00:20:15.55,00:20:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the U.S. Army.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:27.43,00:20:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All manner of government vehicle \Nare converging on subjects.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:31.23,00:20:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in a restricted area, sir.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:32.98,00:20:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,- We need you to come with us. \N- Right. Right.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:35.82,00:20:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, we're gonna go \Nwith these guys.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:38.11,00:20:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll be fun, huh?
Dialogue: 0,00:20:42.78,00:20:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This is wild.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:44.78,00:20:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This is really wild.
Dialogue: 0,00:20:57.80,00:21:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This is unbelievable. \N2700 degrees Celsius at 40,000 feet?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:01.76,00:21:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, \Nit sounds completely implausible.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:04.10,00:21:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Nonetheless, we're ticking off \Nan increase of almost 0.5 percent.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:07.64,00:21:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- Per day? \N- No.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:09.56,00:21:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Per hour.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:10.77,00:21:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Helmsley. We've arrested \Na group of tourists in the hot zone.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:14.02,00:21:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I'll take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:15.48,00:21:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, let's get Satnam \Non the communications link.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:18.28,00:21:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll try and cross-reference \Nthe data.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:20.40,00:21:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a national park. There's not \Nsupposed to be posted fences.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:23.66,00:21:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:25.70,00:21:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We're geologists.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:28.16,00:21:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you usually go digging \Nwith machine guns?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:32.04,00:21:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Major, I'll take care of this. \NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:34.21,00:21:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- What happened to the lake? \N- That's what we're trying to find out.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:37.55,00:21:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We think the entire area \Nhas become unstable.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:39.84,00:21:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you should take your kids \Nand leave, Mr. Curtis.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:44.18,00:21:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not by any chance \Nthe Jackson Curtis...
Dialogue: 0,00:21:46.72,00:21:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,...who wrote Farewell Atlantis, \Nare you?
Dialogue: 0,00:21:51.64,00:21:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The very same.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:54.23,00:21:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's actually dedicated to my mom.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:57.02,00:21:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's great.
Dialogue: 0,00:21:58.82,00:22:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I read a couple of your short stories \Nwhen I was in college. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:02.78,00:22:05.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, \Nyour father is a very talented man.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:05.61,00:22:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- Listen up. \N- It's amazing. I'm reading your book.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:08.12,00:22:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm around day 300, the shuttle has \Njust lost communication with Earth.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:11.62,00:22:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You're one of the lucky few \Nwho bought it.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:13.71,00:22:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,- I didn't buy it. \N- No?
Dialogue: 0,00:22:15.58,00:22:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,My dad gave it to me.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:18.92,00:22:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me ask you something.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:21.17,00:22:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You believe those people \Nwould behave so selflessly...
Dialogue: 0,00:22:23.97,00:22:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,...knowing that their own lives \Nwere at stake?
Dialogue: 0,00:22:26.26,00:22:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope so.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:27.85,00:22:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The critics said I was naive, \Nan unabashed optimist...
Dialogue: 0,00:22:31.31,00:22:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,...but what do they know, right?
Dialogue: 0,00:22:33.14,00:22:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,00:22:34.73,00:22:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- Pleasure. \N- It was a great pleasure meeting you.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:37.56,00:22:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Major, could you escort these \Ngood people to the campgrounds?
Dialogue: 0,00:22:40.57,00:22:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This is yours.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:41.90,00:22:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,- Thank you. \N- Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:43.40,00:22:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,- Take care. \N- Okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:44.65,00:22:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,He was very nice.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:45.95,00:22:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You're just saying that \Nbecause he liked my book.
Dialogue: 0,00:22:53.70,00:22:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like that boy of yours \Nis gonna be smarter than any of us.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:02.05,00:23:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,00:23:03.26,00:23:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I sent Satnam \Nthe temperature reading.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:06.13,00:23:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,My colleagues in Argentina and \NOntario have almost identical data.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:10.18,00:23:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so hot here, \Nwe've had to seal off the mine.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:12.77,00:23:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- Double-checked the numbers? \N- Triple-checked, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:15.60,00:23:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish we were wrong...
Dialogue: 0,00:23:18.27,00:23:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,...but we're not.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:20.44,00:23:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The Earth's crust is destabilizing.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:27.95,00:23:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too early.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:29.41,00:23:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Adrian, \Nyou have to begin the evacuation.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:34.70,00:23:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,My God.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:36.62,00:23:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,All our scientific advances, \Nour fancy machines...
Dialogue: 0,00:23:40.42,00:23:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mayans saw this coming \Nthousands of years ago.
Dialogue: 0,00:23:52.39,00:23:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought we'd have more time.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:02.77,00:24:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:04.69,00:24:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to pack up your family.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:06.49,00:24:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna arrange an airlift for you \Nfrom Delhi.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:09.28,00:24:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:11.41,00:24:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And good luck.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:20.92,00:24:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Ajit.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:24.50,00:24:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We are going on a big ship.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:30.01,00:24:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- That was so cool. \N- Yeah, that was intense.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:32.34,00:24:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,- The helicopters. \N- Craziest place I've seen.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:34.68,00:24:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,- Those helicopters were so cool. \N- Wait. Wait. Wait.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:38.52,00:24:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait. Sorry. One question:
Dialogue: 0,00:24:41.31,00:24:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What did the government guys \Nsay to you?
Dialogue: 0,00:24:48.65,00:24:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they don't like us \Ngoing over their fences...
Dialogue: 0,00:24:52.32,00:24:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,...and that the whole area \Nback there is unstable.
Dialogue: 0,00:24:56.04,00:24:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Unstable. They said "unstable"?
Dialogue: 0,00:24:58.87,00:24:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, unstable.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:02.29,00:25:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's funny.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:04.04,00:25:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go. Have a good one.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:08.80,00:25:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Unstable.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:16.06,00:25:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just Yellowstone, sir.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:18.10,00:25:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Temperatures are rising \Nwith incredible velocity...
Dialogue: 0,00:25:20.89,00:25:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,...in hot zones across the globe.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:22.65,00:25:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you absolutely sure \Nabout this, Adrian?
Dialogue: 0,00:25:25.11,00:25:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Because once we give \Nthese orders...
Dialogue: 0,00:25:26.94,00:25:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,...there's no going back. \NYou understand that?
Dialogue: 0,00:25:29.28,00:25:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid there's no longer \Nany doubt, sir.
Dialogue: 0,00:25:32.36,00:25:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to save what we can. \NAnd we have to move now!
Dialogue: 0,00:26:06.56,00:26:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There's mosquitoes in here. \NDid anybody spray the tent?
Dialogue: 0,00:26:10.78,00:26:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna get that spray tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:12.61,00:26:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They just like you \Nbecause your blood's so sweet.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:16.53,00:26:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, you said you wouldn't work \Non your book.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:19.37,00:26:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What, Lil'bee? I'm not, I'm not. \NI'm just... I'm doing something else.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:23.33,00:26:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me get you ready for... \NReady for bed.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:26.46,00:26:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:30.84,00:26:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you really need all these hats?
Dialogue: 0,00:26:32.84,00:26:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- Where are your Pull-Ups, sweetie? \N- I have them on.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:43.18,00:26:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a listener calling in.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:44.85,00:26:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill from Cooke City, \Nyou're on the Charlie Frost Show.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:48.06,00:26:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Charlie, just wanted to say \NI love your show.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:50.27,00:26:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:51.57,00:26:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,...not afraid to tell the truth.
Dialogue: 0,00:26:53.36,00:26:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Bill. \NWhat is your question?
Dialogue: 0,00:26:55.36,00:26:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to know, \Nwhere is all this gonna start?
Dialogue: 0,00:26:57.74,00:27:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, something like this could only \Noriginate in Hollywood, Bill.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:01.24,00:27:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,They got the Earth \Ncracking under their asses already.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:03.95,00:27:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Our family believes in the gospel \Nof the Lord Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:07.04,00:27:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- We have nothing to fear, Charlie. \N- Good for you, Bill. Thanks for calling.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:10.79,00:27:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Charlie Frost reporting live \Nfrom Yellowstone National Park...
Dialogue: 0,00:27:15.76,00:27:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,...soon to become \Nthe world's largest active volcano.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:21.35,00:27:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be right back, folks.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:26.44,00:27:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mind if I join you? \NI wanted to ask you something.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:29.48,00:27:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I only got a minute.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:31.19,00:27:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. Pickle?
Dialogue: 0,00:27:33.40,00:27:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I was listening to the broadcast \Nand I was wondering...
Dialogue: 0,00:27:36.95,00:27:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,...what exactly is it \Nthat's gonna start in Hollywood?
Dialogue: 0,00:27:40.95,00:27:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the apocalypse.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:42.95,00:27:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,End of days.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:44.87,00:27:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The Judgment Day, \Nthe end of the world, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,00:27:48.58,00:27:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Christians called it the rapture, \Nbut the Mayans knew about it...
Dialogue: 0,00:27:52.21,00:27:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,...the Hopis, the I Ching...
Dialogue: 0,00:27:55.67,00:27:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,...the Bible, kind of...
Dialogue: 0,00:27:58.47,00:27:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Beer?
Dialogue: 0,00:28:00.30,00:28:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah. \N- So look, I gotta eat.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:02.85,00:28:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you download my blog. \NIt's free.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:06.85,00:28:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, \Nwe do appreciate donations.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:10.31,00:28:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,In ancient times, the Mayan people \Nwere the first civilization to discover...
Dialogue: 0,00:28:14.69,00:28:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,...that this planet had \Nan expiration date.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:17.32,00:28:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,According to their calendar...
Dialogue: 0,00:28:18.99,00:28:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,...in the year 2012, \Na cataclysmic event will unfold...
Dialogue: 0,00:28:22.66,00:28:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,...caused by an alignment \Nof the planets in our solar system...
Dialogue: 0,00:28:25.70,00:28:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,...that only happens \Nevery 640,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:29.08,00:28:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, not again.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:31.83,00:28:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty neat, huh? \NI did all the animation myself.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:36.13,00:28:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Just imagine the Earth \Nas an orange.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:39.68,00:28:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You lure them in with humor. \NThen you make them think.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:44.05,00:28:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Our sun will begin to emit \Nsuch extreme amounts of radiation...
Dialogue: 0,00:28:47.89,00:28:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Those little bastards \Nare called neutrinos.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:50.27,00:28:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,...that the core of the Earth will melt. \NThat's the inside part of the orange...
Dialogue: 0,00:28:54.11,00:28:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,...leaving the crust of our planet \Nfree to shift.
Dialogue: 0,00:28:57.44,00:29:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1958, Professor Charles Hapgood \Nnamed it Earth Crust Displacement.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:02.36,00:29:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Albert Einstein did support it.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:05.53,00:29:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,People, we'll get it all.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:06.87,00:29:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The forces of Mother Nature \Nwill be so devastating...
Dialogue: 0,00:29:09.91,00:29:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,...it will bring an end to this world \Non winter solstice, 12-21-12.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:15.96,00:29:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Always remember, folks, \Nyou heard it first from Charlie Frost.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:20.80,00:29:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd have to keep a thing like this \Nunder wraps.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:23.76,00:29:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, just think about it, okay?
Dialogue: 0,00:29:25.97,00:29:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,First, the stock market would go.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:28.77,00:29:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the economy, boom!
Dialogue: 0,00:29:31.19,00:29:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The dollar, boom!
Dialogue: 0,00:29:32.64,00:29:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And then pandemonium in the streets. \NWar, genocide, boom, boom, boom!
Dialogue: 0,00:29:38.32,00:29:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Bullshit. Nobody could keep \Nthat big a secret, Charlie.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:41.65,00:29:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,- Somebody would blow the whistle. \N- Every once in a while...
Dialogue: 0,00:29:44.57,00:29:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,...some poor little sucker tries.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:46.78,00:29:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, like these guys, boom, boom!
Dialogue: 0,00:29:49.66,00:29:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Every one of these guys, \Ndead, dead, dead.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:56.84,00:29:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That's Professor Meyers.
Dialogue: 0,00:29:58.50,00:30:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He ran the Atlantis shuttle program. \NWhy, did you know him?
Dialogue: 0,00:30:01.51,00:30:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he helped me \Nwith research on my book.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:04.09,00:30:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that must have been \Nbefore his "accident. "
Dialogue: 0,00:30:06.85,00:30:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Meyers is dead?
Dialogue: 0,00:30:08.76,00:30:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah, two months ago.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:11.06,00:30:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He was one \Nof my most avid listeners...
Dialogue: 0,00:30:13.98,00:30:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,...and he had it all figured out.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:16.10,00:30:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything the government was doing, \Nwhere and why...
Dialogue: 0,00:30:19.61,00:30:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He even sent me a map.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:22.69,00:30:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A map for what, Charlie? \NWhat's the map for?
Dialogue: 0,00:30:32.08,00:30:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They're building spaceships, man.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:42.55,00:30:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit, man, I have to go...
Dialogue: 0,00:30:44.63,00:30:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,...because I gotta get back to Earth.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:48.10,00:30:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- But do you got a traveler for the road? \N- This is my last...
Dialogue: 0,00:30:50.97,00:30:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that'll be all right. But, anyway, \NI really enjoyed most of this.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:54.31,00:30:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:55.64,00:30:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. Hey, guess what.
Dialogue: 0,00:30:57.65,00:31:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- They're selling seats. \N- Put me down for three.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:00.52,00:31:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No, guys like you and me \Ndon't have a chance.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:02.82,00:31:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd have to be Bill Gates \Nor Rupert Murdoch...
Dialogue: 0,00:31:05.45,00:31:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,...or some Russian billionaire \Nor something.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:07.61,00:31:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep it down, my kids are sleeping.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:09.49,00:31:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Get them out of Yellowstone.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:12.41,00:31:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's gonna get ugly here.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:16.04,00:31:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have anything \Nfor mosquito bites?
Dialogue: 0,00:31:18.29,00:31:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Before or after?
Dialogue: 0,00:31:21.71,00:31:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd get before and after.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:23.21,00:31:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop scratching. \NYou're gonna get it all infected.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:26.13,00:31:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to make a stop \Nat the grocery store.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:28.47,00:31:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Mrs. Birnbaum. \NShe's my teacher, she's on TV.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:32.39,00:31:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is Grayson's Market, which \Nwas open for business at the time...
Dialogue: 0,00:31:35.73,00:31:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,...but fortunately, there were \Nno fatalities or injuries reported.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:39.31,00:31:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It really is a miracle \Nthat no one got hurt.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:42.44,00:31:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello? Oh, hi, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:45.32,00:31:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see what happened \Nto our supermarket?
Dialogue: 0,00:31:50.41,00:31:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,She wants us to come home.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:52.66,00:31:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,is this even possible?
Dialogue: 0,00:31:53.99,00:31:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We worked every option \Nthrough the night.
Dialogue: 0,00:31:56.33,00:32:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The good news, consensus is that four \Nof the arks will be operational in time.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:00.67,00:32:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Only four? You call that good news?
Dialogue: 0,00:32:02.50,00:32:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We can save over 400,000 people.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:05.17,00:32:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,To me, sir, \Nthat's nothing short of a miracle.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:07.42,00:32:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But we have to initiate \Nthe boarding process now. Thomas.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:11.60,00:32:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't have a choice.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:13.51,00:32:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You have got to convince them.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:18.06,00:32:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, I'll try to keep this brief.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:19.98,00:32:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,According to the latest information \Nfrom Yellowsto...
Dialogue: 0,00:32:23.19,00:32:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,- Please continue, Adrian. \N- Thank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:26.36,00:32:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The temperature \Nof the subterranean crust...
Dialogue: 0,00:32:28.90,00:32:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,...that is, the cement that holds \Nour land mass in place...
Dialogue: 0,00:32:32.82,00:32:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,...is increasing at a rapid rate, \Nmuch faster than anticipated.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:36.29,00:32:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,As a result, we've observed \Nextreme polar instability.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:39.54,00:32:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The magnetic fields have decreased \Nby more than 80 percent...
Dialogue: 0,00:32:42.50,00:32:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,...in the last 48 hours.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:44.21,00:32:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,How much time do we have, \NDr. Helmsley?
Dialogue: 0,00:32:49.51,00:32:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Two, maybe three days, \Nif we're lucky.
Dialogue: 0,00:32:52.22,00:32:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you speak about luck \Nin such a situation?
Dialogue: 0,00:32:56.06,00:32:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Apologies, Mr. Prime Minister. I...
Dialogue: 0,00:32:58.98,00:33:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I meant no disrespect.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:02.56,00:33:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid the longer we wait, \Nthe more luck plays its part.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:12.91,00:33:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,My friends...
Dialogue: 0,00:33:15.58,00:33:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,...I recommend \Nwe evacuate immediately.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:20.37,00:33:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,If any of you have objections...
Dialogue: 0,00:33:24.46,00:33:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,...please speak now.
Dialogue: 0,00:33:27.00,00:33:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In the blue corner...
Dialogue: 0,00:33:30.26,00:33:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,...38 victories, 34 knockouts...
Dialogue: 0,00:33:32.38,00:33:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,...the fighting machine \Nfrom the Ukraine...
Dialogue: 0,00:33:35.43,00:33:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,...the undefeated number-one ranked \Nheavyweight challenger:
Dialogue: 0,00:33:39.98,00:33:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Zultan Balashin!
Dialogue: 0,00:34:07.63,00:34:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill the bastard, Zultan.
Dialogue: 0,00:34:10.63,00:34:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen...
Dialogue: 0,00:34:13.18,00:34:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,...let's get ready to rumble!
Dialogue: 0,00:34:20.47,00:34:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Zultan!
Dialogue: 0,00:34:59.43,00:35:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,One, two, three...
Dialogue: 0,00:35:04.23,00:35:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Caltech believes that the half-mile \Nfissure running through Westwood...
Dialogue: 0,00:35:07.73,00:35:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,...has released \Nmost of the surface tension.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:09.98,00:35:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,"Life will soon return to normal," \NMayor Gonzales said...
Dialogue: 0,00:35:13.03,00:35:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- ... at an early news conference. \N- Okay, guys. Almost home.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:18.45,00:35:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Rise and shine.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:30.21,00:35:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, you're free.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:33.67,00:35:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- Thank God. \N- Mommy.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:37.72,00:35:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, sweetheart.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:43.52,00:35:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Gordon!
Dialogue: 0,00:35:46.14,00:35:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, buddy boy.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:49.10,00:35:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Good time? Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,00:35:51.57,00:35:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,God, I missed you.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:53.40,00:35:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,00:35:54.57,00:35:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- Who wants pancakes? Come on. \N- Me.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:01.24,00:36:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,- Thanks for bringing them home early. \N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:05.58,00:36:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Pancakes?
Dialogue: 0,00:36:08.71,00:36:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Late for work.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:21.14,00:36:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yes, hello? \N- Curtis, where are you?
Dialogue: 0,00:36:24.01,00:36:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,- Just getting back from vacation, sir. \N- Good. That is good.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:27.77,00:36:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I will send the jet \Nto pick up Alec and Oleg.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:30.31,00:36:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuri bear, tell him to bring \Nthe raincoat for Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:33.44,00:36:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's in the Range Rover. \N- Curtis.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:35.94,00:36:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah? \N- Get my boys as fast as you can.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:38.28,00:36:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm hurtling towards you \Nas we speak, sir.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:40.45,00:36:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. That is good.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:57.13,00:36:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Curtis, you're late.
Dialogue: 0,00:36:58.63,00:37:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning to you too.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:04.85,00:37:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, be careful with our stuff. \NDon't get your dirt on it.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:08.14,00:37:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Idiot.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:16.48,00:37:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Took you a while, Mr. Curtis.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:22.45,00:37:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your problem?
Dialogue: 0,00:37:23.99,00:37:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Be more careful.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:25.49,00:37:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He did that on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:27.20,00:37:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, have a safe trip, \Nyou little bastards.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:30.33,00:37:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you're laughing, Curtis...
Dialogue: 0,00:37:31.08,00:37:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,...but we have tickets \Nto go on a big ship.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:34.17,00:37:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We will live...
Dialogue: 0,00:37:35.92,00:37:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,...and you will die.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:49.64,00:37:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Folks, did you hear that?
Dialogue: 0,00:37:51.69,00:37:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The authorities in L.A. \Nsay there's nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,00:37:56.27,00:37:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd love to see their dumb faces...
Dialogue: 0,00:37:58.90,00:38:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,...when Malibu and Beverly Hills...
Dialogue: 0,00:38:01.53,00:38:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,...get sucked into the gurgling maw \Nof the Pacific.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:05.32,00:38:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Where they gonna plug in \Ntheir electric cars then?
Dialogue: 0,00:38:12.29,00:38:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hey. is this your plane? \N- Yes.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:14.42,00:38:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- Are you a pilot? \N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:16.04,00:38:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna rent it. \NI'll give you anything.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:18.09,00:38:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Here. \NThis is a very expensive watch.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:20.01,00:38:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,My editor gave it to me when \Nhe thought I was gonna be somebody.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:25.43,00:38:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,00:38:26.97,00:38:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,- Stop what you're doing. \N- Jackson?
Dialogue: 0,00:38:28.68,00:38:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to me. I've rented a plane. \NPack up the kids.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:31.47,00:38:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,- I'm gonna be there in five minutes. \N- Plane? What?
Dialogue: 0,00:38:34.31,00:38:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We're gonna do our regular Saturday. \NNoah has music and Lil has karate.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:37.98,00:38:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Not that we'd expect him \Nto remember.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:39.82,00:38:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Kate, California is going down.
Dialogue: 0,00:38:42.11,00:38:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, could you call me back \Nwhen you calm down?
Dialogue: 0,00:38:45.74,00:38:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Mommy? Why is daddy so crazy?
Dialogue: 0,00:38:49.91,00:38:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Mommy!
Dialogue: 0,00:39:01.34,00:39:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone hold on to each other.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:03.51,00:39:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- No, Lilly! \N- Hold Mommy's hand and stay close.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:08.80,00:39:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy!
Dialogue: 0,00:39:10.06,00:39:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,00:39:11.51,00:39:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's safer under here!
Dialogue: 0,00:39:13.89,00:39:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Get in the fucking car right now!
Dialogue: 0,00:39:17.65,00:39:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Move your ass! Move!
Dialogue: 0,00:39:19.31,00:39:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,- Come on, kids. \N- Get up!
Dialogue: 0,00:39:20.77,00:39:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,- Move. Quick, quick! \N- Move!
Dialogue: 0,00:39:23.11,00:39:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Go! Now!
Dialogue: 0,00:39:26.32,00:39:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,- Come on, let's go. \N- Run! Don't look back!
Dialogue: 0,00:39:28.82,00:39:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- Come on! \N- Take her! Get in, honey, get in.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:32.45,00:39:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,My hats.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:35.54,00:39:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Lilly, get in!
Dialogue: 0,00:39:38.29,00:39:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Get in!
Dialogue: 0,00:39:39.50,00:39:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,- Buckle up! \N- Lilly.
Dialogue: 0,00:39:49.80,00:39:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:04.53,00:40:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Jackson, hurry up. Look behind you.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:08.07,00:40:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,- Holy...! \N- Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:14.70,00:40:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Get out of herw! \NGet out of the way!
Dialogue: 0,00:40:16.62,00:40:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,- Move it! \N- Hold on to those eggs, dear.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:19.37,00:40:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,- Come on! \N- Come on, you old bags!
Dialogue: 0,00:40:23.46,00:40:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Sidewalk, sidewalk! Tree! Tree!
Dialogue: 0,00:40:27.38,00:40:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,God. Carwful.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:32.89,00:40:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody, hang on.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:37.81,00:40:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:39.14,00:40:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Careful, careful.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:45.07,00:40:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yikes. That stinks.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:52.49,00:40:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We gotta get to the airport.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:54.49,00:40:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, take the freeway, \Nit'll be half the time.
Dialogue: 0,00:40:59.91,00:41:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:07.76,00:41:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:10.63,00:41:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We gotta get to the other side \Nof the freeway.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:14.26,00:41:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy!
Dialogue: 0,00:41:27.69,00:41:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,- Dad, look! \N- No. We're not gonna make it! Careful!
Dialogue: 0,00:41:38.95,00:41:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- No, Daddy! \N- Dad, look. Dad, look.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:42.62,00:41:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no!
Dialogue: 0,00:41:56.80,00:41:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been upgraded to a 10.9 \Nby the guys at Harvard.
Dialogue: 0,00:41:59.47,00:42:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What does Caltech have to say?
Dialogue: 0,00:42:01.14,00:42:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole city of Pasadena \Nwas wiped out just a few minutes ago.
Dialogue: 0,00:42:05.48,00:42:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,This is coming in from Coachella \NValley out near Joshua Tree.
Dialogue: 0,00:42:08.61,00:42:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That canyon? \NThat wasn't there this morning.
Dialogue: 0,00:42:10.90,00:42:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And 400 miles further north, \NPoint Reyes, same thing.
Dialogue: 0,00:42:16.49,00:42:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The San Andreas Fault is shifting.
Dialogue: 0,00:42:18.62,00:42:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. And all major sister faults \Nin the Bay Area.
Dialogue: 0,00:42:20.95,00:42:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole Pacific plate \Nis destabilizing.
Dialogue: 0,00:42:31.51,00:42:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold my hand. Stay close to me.
Dialogue: 0,00:42:34.59,00:42:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,00:42:36.18,00:42:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- Who's that? \N- Our pilot!
Dialogue: 0,00:42:38.22,00:42:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, jeez. It's our pilot.
Dialogue: 0,00:42:41.02,00:42:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Gordon. Gordon, you can fly.
Dialogue: 0,00:42:43.10,00:42:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, I've only had a couple of \Nlessons in a single-engine plane only.
Dialogue: 0,00:42:46.73,00:42:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,- You're the guy. \N- I am not the guy.
Dialogue: 0,00:42:48.52,00:42:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,- Trust me, you're the guy. \N- I'm not being modest about this.
Dialogue: 0,00:42:52.57,00:42:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, kids. \NGordon's gonna get us out of here.
Dialogue: 0,00:42:55.03,00:42:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That plane has multiple engines.
Dialogue: 0,00:42:58.41,00:43:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Jackson!
Dialogue: 0,00:43:15.26,00:43:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,- T's and P's, T's and P's. \N- T and P?
Dialogue: 0,00:43:17.22,00:43:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,- Temperatures and pressures. \N- Go!
Dialogue: 0,00:43:19.05,00:43:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- I've gotta do my preflight check. \N- Let him concentrate.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:21.81,00:43:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He has no experience.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:23.31,00:43:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:26.23,00:43:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,- Gordon, go. \N- Come on.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:27.90,00:43:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- Gordon! \N- Go, go, go!
Dialogue: 0,00:43:32.40,00:43:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,- We're not there yet. \N- Gordon, take off.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:35.90,00:43:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,- Punch it, punch it! \N- I have to get to 85 knots.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:38.28,00:43:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- Eighty's good. \N- Oh, screw it. Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:45.79,00:43:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Okay, we're up.
Dialogue: 0,00:43:56.97,00:43:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Higher, higher!
Dialogue: 0,00:44:35.51,00:44:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:04.58,00:45:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Lilly, go sit with your brother.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:11.33,00:45:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't understand. How did you know \Nthis was gonna happen?
Dialogue: 0,00:45:14.84,00:45:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not just California.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:17.05,00:45:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the whole goddamn world \Nthat's going to shit.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:19.92,00:45:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I met this guy in Yellowstone, \Nthis crazy guy.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:22.22,00:45:24.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He's been right about everything \Nthat's happened so far.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:25.05,00:45:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And he said the government \Nis building spaceships.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:27.52,00:45:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- I don't know what, but something. \N- Ships?
Dialogue: 0,00:45:29.85,00:45:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, places where we can be safe.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:32.15,00:45:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows where they are. \NHe's got a map.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:34.86,00:45:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Jackson.
Dialogue: 0,00:45:36.36,00:45:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Kate, you gotta just trust me on this, \Nokay?
Dialogue: 0,00:45:38.65,00:45:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Guys, look.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:03.84,00:46:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a twist and a turn \NTo each lesson you learn
Dialogue: 0,00:46:07.22,00:46:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,First you're up, then you're bust \NLivin' life on a crust
Dialogue: 0,00:46:10.73,00:46:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But it ain't the end of the world, buddy
Dialogue: 0,00:46:14.06,00:46:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only the end of this song
Dialogue: 0,00:46:17.06,00:46:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a gas, been a flip \NBeen a hell of a trip
Dialogue: 0,00:46:20.65,00:46:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But it ain't the end of the world
Dialogue: 0,00:46:26.78,00:46:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:28.41,00:46:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:29.66,00:46:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You got fans, Tony.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:33.08,00:46:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a call for you. \NYou want me to take a message?
Dialogue: 0,00:46:35.83,00:46:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's all right, Kevin. I got it.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:43.22,00:46:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hello. \N- Dad?
Dialogue: 0,00:46:45.43,00:46:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Adrian.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:46.93,00:46:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember when I told you \Nabout that dam in China?
Dialogue: 0,00:46:50.68,00:46:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,00:46:52.14,00:46:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's happening, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:02.78,00:47:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,They'd probably shoot me \Nif they knew that I told you.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:08.07,00:47:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody's gonna shoot you, son. \NThey need you.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:11.45,00:47:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The president has ordered us \Nto clear out the White House.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:15.25,00:47:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,About time somebody cleaned up \Nthat mess.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:20.96,00:47:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,00:47:22.92,00:47:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What exactly is the course \Nof the Genesis right now?
Dialogue: 0,00:47:26.26,00:47:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all good, Adrian.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:28.80,00:47:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you be worrying \Nabout your old man now.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:31.97,00:47:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You got more important things \Nto do now.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:37.35,00:47:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You know...
Dialogue: 0,00:47:39.86,00:47:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,...your mom and I, we...
Dialogue: 0,00:47:42.32,00:47:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We had one hell of a great life, son.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:46.99,00:47:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And the best part about that...
Dialogue: 0,00:47:51.49,00:47:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,...is we had \None hell of a great kid too.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:57.50,00:47:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you lookie here.
Dialogue: 0,00:47:59.13,00:48:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The Genesis...
Dialogue: 0,00:48:01.21,00:48:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,...it's a pretty big ship, son.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:04.17,00:48:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So don't you write your old man off \Njust yet.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:08.51,00:48:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides...
Dialogue: 0,00:48:11.30,00:48:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,...you know I couldn't leave \NTony alone.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:14.43,00:48:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that old fool \Ncan't keep decent time by himself.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:20.69,00:48:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I love you, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:28.28,00:48:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I love you too, son.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:30.66,00:48:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,God knows I do.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:45.84,00:48:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Kevin, I want a double.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:48.84,00:48:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,- Harry. \N- I need a double right now.
Dialogue: 0,00:48:56.64,00:48:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, son.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:01.40,00:49:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,After 25 years on the wagon, \Nare you out of your mind?
Dialogue: 0,00:49:21.83,00:49:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,- What are you doing? \N- Gotta go.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:23.42,00:49:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's against regulation. \N- Careful, careful.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:30.76,00:49:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,- Anything? \N- Yeah, there's fuel.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:32.43,00:49:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Fill it up. I'm gonna find Charlie.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:34.35,00:49:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy, wait. I wanna come with you.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:36.18,00:49:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- No, no. Lil. Lil, no! \N- It's all right. Just fill it up.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:39.27,00:49:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,- We'll be back. \N- Jackson, hurry, please.
Dialogue: 0,00:49:41.77,00:49:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm standing here \Nat the highest point...
Dialogue: 0,00:49:44.94,00:49:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,...of what is the rim of the world's \Nlargest super-volcano...
Dialogue: 0,00:49:50.07,00:49:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- ... Mount Bighorn, elevation 2779 feet. \N- Charlie! Charlie! Charlie!
Dialogue: 0,00:49:56.95,00:50:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I can only hope that all of you \Nhave made your peace with God...
Dialogue: 0,00:50:01.54,00:50:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- He's gotta be around somewhere. \N- Let's go back.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:04.04,00:50:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no. We gotta find Charlie \Nbecause he's got a map.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:06.88,00:50:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a secret map, \Nlike in the Pirate movies.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:09.34,00:50:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,- We gotta work as a team, okay? \N- Okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:11.30,00:50:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, come on.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:13.13,00:50:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Call Mommy and tell her \Nwe're gonna be 5 minutes late.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:20.81,00:50:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hello? \N- I need to talk to Mommy.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:22.98,00:50:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- It's Lilly. \N- Sweetheart, where are you?
Dialogue: 0,00:50:25.31,00:50:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hi, Mommy. \N- Let me speak to Daddy, sweetie.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:28.02,00:50:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He can't talk right now. \NHe's driving really, really bad.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:33.07,00:50:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Any minute now, \Nthe fireworks are gonna start.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:35.87,00:50:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is that? \NWho's speaking in the car?
Dialogue: 0,00:50:37.83,00:50:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not in the car. He's on \Na mountain waiting for fireworks.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:41.04,00:50:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,- Fireworks? What fireworks? \N- Daddy. Daddy, over there.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:44.33,00:50:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,...to send all of Yellowstone \Ninto outer space?
Dialogue: 0,00:50:47.04,00:50:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Good job, Lilly. Good job.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:50.50,00:50:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me talk to Mom.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:52.17,00:50:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- Kate, we got him. \N- Jackson, bring back my child now.
Dialogue: 0,00:50:58.85,00:51:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. You stay here \Nand guard the ship...
Dialogue: 0,00:51:02.02,00:51:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,- ... and I'm gonna go talk to the pirate. \N- Okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:04.89,00:51:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,...your race, your country, your god.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:07.73,00:51:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you're a Christian or \Na Buddhist or Muslim or Rastafarian...
Dialogue: 0,00:51:12.61,00:51:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,- ... by tomorrow we will all be one! \N- Charlie.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:16.03,00:51:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- Jackson. What are you doing here? \N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:18.07,00:51:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,- I thought you were toast. \N- No. Where are the spaceships?
Dialogue: 0,00:51:21.08,00:51:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way \Nyou can make it there.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:23.37,00:51:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a plane. You could come \Nwith us, but we gotta leave right now.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:35.26,00:51:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Fly, birdies.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:38.05,00:51:39.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Fly!
Dialogue: 0,00:51:40.05,00:51:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is this your kid?
Dialogue: 0,00:51:42.56,00:51:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the goddamn map?
Dialogue: 0,00:51:43.97,00:51:45.89,Default,,0,0,0,,- We're going live. \N- Where is it?
Dialogue: 0,00:51:46.06,00:51:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Charlie. Focus. Where's the map? \NWhere?
Dialogue: 0,00:51:48.98,00:51:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in the camper.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:50.23,00:51:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Where in the camper?
Dialogue: 0,00:51:51.44,00:51:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In the map section \Non the conspiracy shelf.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:54.94,00:51:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Dewey decimal system.
Dialogue: 0,00:51:57.03,00:51:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Between Roswell...
Dialogue: 0,00:51:59.62,00:52:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,...and Marilyn Monroe.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:11.09,00:52:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's starting.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:21.10,00:52:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure you don't wanna come with, \Nman?
Dialogue: 0,00:52:23.76,00:52:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so beautiful. I'm gonna stay.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:28.14,00:52:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:32.94,00:52:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This marks the last day \Nof the United States of America.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:39.78,00:52:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And, by tomorrow, all of mankind.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:43.28,00:52:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And we will be visible \Nfrom the Milky Way...
Dialogue: 0,00:52:45.95,00:52:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,...as a tiny little puff of smoke.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:49.29,00:52:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm watching the earth crumble \Nbefore my eyes.
Dialogue: 0,00:52:54.80,00:53:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The giant ash cloud \Ncreated by this super-volcano...
Dialogue: 0,00:53:00.55,00:53:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,...will first envelop Vegas...
Dialogue: 0,00:53:03.14,00:53:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,...and then St. Louis...
Dialogue: 0,00:53:05.31,00:53:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,...and then Chicago...
Dialogue: 0,00:53:07.47,00:53:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,...and then, at long last...
Dialogue: 0,00:53:09.69,00:53:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,...Washington, D.C. \Nwill have its lights go out!
Dialogue: 0,00:53:14.32,00:53:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,- That guy's crazy, right, Daddy? \N- I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:20.20,00:53:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This is ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:21.82,00:53:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Been over half an hour. \NI tell you, the guy's a nut job.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:24.58,00:53:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it, Gordon.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:26.33,00:53:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Noah, hand me the phone again.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:50.35,00:53:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy, what was that?
Dialogue: 0,00:53:53.40,00:53:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing. Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,00:53:56.32,00:53:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I have goose bumps, people.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:21.38,00:54:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish you could see \Nwhat I'm seeing, people.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:24.43,00:54:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish you could be here with me!
Dialogue: 0,00:54:27.68,00:54:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, baby.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:31.06,00:54:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring it on!
Dialogue: 0,00:54:33.23,00:54:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Always remember, folks...
Dialogue: 0,00:54:35.73,00:54:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,...you heard it first from Charlie!
Dialogue: 0,00:54:54.87,00:54:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy, it's following us.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:56.42,00:54:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't look! Get on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,00:54:58.09,00:55:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Get on the ground and hold on. \NDon't look back.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:00.42,00:55:03.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't look back. Just look at me. \NLook at me. Do I look scared?
Dialogue: 0,00:55:08.68,00:55:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, hold on, baby. Hold on tight.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:18.15,00:55:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy, we're on fire.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:28.28,00:55:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,There it is! There they are.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:35.54,00:55:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's them.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:37.00,00:55:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's them. It's them.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:40.46,00:55:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Mommy!
Dialogue: 0,00:55:45.22,00:55:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeez.
Dialogue: 0,00:55:53.31,00:55:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- No, Daddy. \N- Hang on, baby. Hang on!
Dialogue: 0,00:55:58.69,00:55:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Daddy!
Dialogue: 0,00:56:08.99,00:56:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my Go...
Dialogue: 0,00:56:10.66,00:56:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,- Mommy. \N- Take her, take her. I'll be right back.
Dialogue: 0,00:56:19.83,00:56:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,- Come here, Lil. Grab my hand. \N- Come on, Lil. Lilly, you okay?
Dialogue: 0,00:56:23.05,00:56:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Aliens, Roswell \Nand Marilyn Monroe...
Dialogue: 0,00:56:25.55,00:56:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Maps! Maps!
Dialogue: 0,00:56:27.55,00:56:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- Everybody on? Are we ready? \N- Jackson!
Dialogue: 0,00:56:33.56,00:56:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,- Kate, where is he? What's he doing? \N- I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,00:56:39.69,00:56:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,00:56:49.61,00:56:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,- Daddy! \N- No!
Dialogue: 0,00:56:54.70,00:56:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, my God. \N- Kate, we have to go.
Dialogue: 0,00:56:58.04,00:56:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No. We're not going anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,00:56:59.79,00:57:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,- Kids, buckle up, we're leaving. \N- This is my dad. We're gonna wait.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:08.55,00:57:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,00:57:10.47,00:57:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy!
Dialogue: 0,00:57:15.56,00:57:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! \NWait, Gordon, I see something.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:18.64,00:57:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,00:57:24.77,00:57:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Daddy!
Dialogue: 0,00:57:30.40,00:57:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Slow down!
Dialogue: 0,00:57:31.91,00:57:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Jackson, run!
Dialogue: 0,00:57:33.91,00:57:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Jackson, take my hand. Jackson.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:36.58,00:57:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,- Dad, hurry! \N- Run!
Dialogue: 0,00:57:39.66,00:57:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We're running out of runway. \NFor God's sakes, Kate, pull him up.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:42.92,00:57:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,- Jackson, reach for my hand. \N- Dad, you can make it, come on.
Dialogue: 0,00:57:46.63,00:57:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy!
Dialogue: 0,00:57:52.43,00:57:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, buckle in. Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,00:57:55.51,00:57:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, faster. Faster.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:17.12,00:58:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang on.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:20.08,00:58:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,- Go faster. \N- I'm trying.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:39.64,00:58:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. We're good!
Dialogue: 0,00:58:41.81,00:58:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,- We're good. \N- We're okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:58:48.02,00:58:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So now that you got your map, \Nwhere are we going?
Dialogue: 0,00:59:02.50,00:59:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We're gonna need a bigger plane.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:11.96,00:59:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you just said that, Mom. \NYeah, you just said that.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:14.68,00:59:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't remember \Nthat you just said that?
Dialogue: 0,00:59:16.84,00:59:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's okay. That's okay.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:20.22,00:59:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, Ma, I am going to call you \Nnext week, same time.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:24.85,00:59:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay?
Dialogue: 0,00:59:26.27,00:59:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You take care now. \NTake care of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:32.03,00:59:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir?
Dialogue: 0,00:59:34.44,00:59:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you need to see this.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:39.74,00:59:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The South American continent \Nhas been ravaged...
Dialogue: 0,00:59:42.08,00:59:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,...by a series of major earthquakes.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:43.95,00:59:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The death toll is expected \Nto be well over 2 million people.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:47.21,00:59:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The devastation in Rio de Janeiro \Nis beyond imagination.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:50.63,00:59:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Two 8.5 tremors have left \Nthe people in the streets...
Dialogue: 0,00:59:53.80,00:59:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,...desperately fighting \Nfor the last remaining resources.
Dialogue: 0,00:59:56.59,01:00:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In the last hour, we received this video from Globo News, Brazil.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:07.44,01:00:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Fear and chaos have spread \Nthroughout the globe, as in London...
Dialogue: 0,01:00:10.65,01:00:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,...where the 30th Olympic Games \Nhave just been suspended.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:13.65,01:00:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Hundreds of thousands are marching \Ntowards 10 Downing Street...
Dialogue: 0,01:00:16.74,01:00:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,...demanding a lift \Nof the information blackout.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:19.70,01:00:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We've had thousands of calls. \NWe had to shut it down.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:22.45,01:00:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We're receiving reports \Nfrom all across the globe.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:25.20,01:00:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Millions upon millions \Nof distraught masses...
Dialogue: 0,01:00:27.62,01:00:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,...are gathering in public places, \Nconverging in desperate prayer.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:31.00,01:00:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Preachers of many \Nreligious denominations...
Dialogue: 0,01:00:33.25,01:00:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,...have taken their message \Nof the end...
Dialogue: 0,01:00:35.34,01:00:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,...to the strwets all over the U.S.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:37.13,01:00:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Repent. There is still time.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:42.51,01:00:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. President.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:44.22,01:00:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to get you on Air Force One \Nimmediately.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:48.94,01:00:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a moment with Adrian.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:50.44,01:00:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No disrespect, \Nbut we simply do not have time.
Dialogue: 0,01:00:52.73,01:00:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Make time.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:06.75,01:01:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you ever meet my wife, \NDorothy?
Dialogue: 0,01:01:09.87,01:01:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No, sir. I didn't have that honor.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:13.75,01:01:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,She was in and out of it \Ntowards the end.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:17.80,01:01:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The night before she passed on, \Nshe took my hand and she told me:
Dialogue: 0,01:01:21.97,01:01:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,"I think you should have a lottery.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:26.64,01:01:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone should \Nhave a chance to go. "
Dialogue: 0,01:01:32.94,01:01:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe that's what \Nwe should have done.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:38.44,01:01:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be the last president \Nof the United States of America.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:43.07,01:01:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know how that feels, son?
Dialogue: 0,01:01:46.28,01:01:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No one could have \Nsaved the country, sir.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:50.50,01:01:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think...
Dialogue: 0,01:01:52.62,01:01:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I think people have a right to know.
Dialogue: 0,01:01:55.96,01:01:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, I'll take care of that.
Dialogue: 0,01:02:00.47,01:02:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on now.
Dialogue: 0,01:02:03.64,01:02:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Not without you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,01:02:06.22,01:02:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You get on that plane, son.
Dialogue: 0,01:02:09.98,01:02:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a brave new world \Nyou're heading to.
Dialogue: 0,01:02:13.35,01:02:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And a young scientist \Nis gonna be worth 20 old politicians.
Dialogue: 0,01:02:44.51,01:02:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You, be careful \Nwith the landing gear.
Dialogue: 0,01:02:47.18,01:02:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Easy, gringo. I know what I doing.
Dialogue: 0,01:02:49.68,01:02:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Attention. The National Guard \Nhas informed us...
Dialogue: 0,01:02:52.35,01:02:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,...that an extremely hazardous \Nash cloud...
Dialogue: 0,01:02:54.48,01:02:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,...is headed for Las Vegas.
Dialogue: 0,01:02:56.06,01:02:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,01:02:57.52,01:03:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone move indoors \Nimmediately.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:00.19,01:03:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,- Sir, you can't stay here. \N- I have plane here.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:02.57,01:03:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not safe. Move it!
Dialogue: 0,01:03:04.74,01:03:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Move it!
Dialogue: 0,01:03:10.91,01:03:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,My fellow Americans...
Dialogue: 0,01:03:13.83,01:03:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,...this will be the last time \NI address you.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:17.92,01:03:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,As you know...
Dialogue: 0,01:03:19.96,01:03:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,...catastrophe has struck \Nour nation...
Dialogue: 0,01:03:24.38,01:03:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,...has struck the world.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:26.68,01:03:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I could tell you...
Dialogue: 0,01:03:29.05,01:03:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,...we could prevent \Nthe coming destruction.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:32.64,01:03:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We cannot.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:35.10,01:03:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, none of us are strangers.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:38.86,01:03:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Today...
Dialogue: 0,01:03:40.19,01:03:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,...we are one family \Nstepping into the darkness together.
Dialogue: 0,01:03:45.57,01:03:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We are a nation of many religions...
Dialogue: 0,01:03:48.07,01:03:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,...but I believe these words \Nreflect the spirit of all of our faiths:
Dialogue: 0,01:03:55.96,01:03:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The Lord is my shepherd, I shall...
Dialogue: 0,01:04:00.38,01:04:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,People! Keep away \Nfrom the doors and windows.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:03.88,01:04:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What are we gonna do? \NWhere are we gonna go?
Dialogue: 0,01:04:06.22,01:04:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Silberman.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:08.64,01:04:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- Tamara. \N- What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,01:04:10.80,01:04:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,- Excuse me. \N- She's a patient, honey.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:13.64,01:04:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, \NI have a private plane out there.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:16.60,01:04:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,- Karpov! \N- We need help.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:18.06,01:04:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yuri! \N- Takeoffs are canceled.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:19.65,01:04:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,- Curtis, you're... \N- You knew. This whole time you knew.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:22.44,01:04:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've got a way out of here, right? \NYou got a plane?
Dialogue: 0,01:04:25.49,01:04:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,My family, take us with. \NPlease. Please.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:27.78,01:04:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss. Boss.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:29.74,01:04:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I found us a plane, an Antonov.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:31.87,01:04:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They were about to take off, \Nbut the tower didn't let them.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:34.74,01:04:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But can you still fly that thing?
Dialogue: 0,01:04:37.16,01:04:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, boss. But I need copilot.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:40.38,01:04:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Gordon's a pilot.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:44.05,01:04:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm not. I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:45.84,01:04:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, he is. Great pilot. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:49.26,01:04:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,01:04:50.59,01:04:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Honey, this is... \NJackson, stop saying I'm a pilot.
Dialogue: 0,01:04:53.51,01:04:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Hey, stop!
Dialogue: 0,01:04:56.06,01:04:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't go out there. Come back!
Dialogue: 0,01:05:03.69,01:05:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Move back, people.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:05.48,01:05:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Get away from the glass!
Dialogue: 0,01:05:11.62,01:05:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, that's a big plane.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:14.78,01:05:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Russian.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:17.29,01:05:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,- Let's move, everybody. Come on. \N- Run!
Dialogue: 0,01:05:19.29,01:05:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,- Yeah, let's go, let's go. \N- Boys, come on.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:24.79,01:05:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- Gordon, where are you? \N- Where did you go?
Dialogue: 0,01:05:26.88,01:05:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm up here in the cockpit. \NHurry up.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:30.59,01:05:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God. Not again.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:40.64,01:05:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, look at these.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:42.27,01:05:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Las Vegas Auto Show.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:44.81,01:05:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We had VIP tickets for that.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:47.40,01:05:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's fantastic. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:49.03,01:05:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Check the main bus for hydraulics, \NI'll balance the tanks.
Dialogue: 0,01:05:52.11,01:05:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,01:05:55.03,01:05:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, okay, okay. I'm trying, okay? \NI'm trying.
Dialogue: 0,01:06:06.42,01:06:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,01:06:07.92,01:06:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, when I say go, \Nyou push all this down at once, okay?
Dialogue: 0,01:06:11.34,01:06:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,- Okay. \N- Go!
Dialogue: 0,01:06:17.31,01:06:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,- What the hell was that? \N- I don't know, but it's not good.
Dialogue: 0,01:06:23.40,01:06:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,- Push. \N- Pushing.
Dialogue: 0,01:06:24.85,01:06:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,01:06:29.99,01:06:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going down! \NWe're going down!
Dialogue: 0,01:06:38.79,01:06:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are the flaps? \NThe flaps are not down.
Dialogue: 0,01:06:41.33,01:06:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be the pumps. Take over.
Dialogue: 0,01:06:43.46,01:06:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Take over? \NWhat do you mean, take over?
Dialogue: 0,01:06:48.17,01:06:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- Sasha! \N- Relax!
Dialogue: 0,01:06:49.67,01:06:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Sit down!
Dialogue: 0,01:06:55.09,01:06:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,God. God. Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:00.43,01:07:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- Oh, God. \N- Okay, I think I got it.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:02.18,01:07:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,- Sasha, now! \N- Okay, okay. Take a deep breath.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:05.85,01:07:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull!
Dialogue: 0,01:07:08.94,01:07:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, baby. \NLift your big ass for Sasha!
Dialogue: 0,01:07:15.95,01:07:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,- Pull! Pull! \N- Come on.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:30.84,01:07:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Mommy.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:34.05,01:07:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Was that the Eiffel Tower?
Dialogue: 0,01:07:36.38,01:07:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I think so.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:45.85,01:07:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen...
Dialogue: 0,01:07:47.90,01:07:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,...we are on our way to China.
Dialogue: 0,01:07:52.11,01:07:55.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. That is good, huh?
Dialogue: 0,01:10:17.92,01:10:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, look. The new Bentley.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:19.46,01:10:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Our father had one on order.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:21.63,01:10:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We were supposed \Nto get it next year.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:23.89,01:10:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But then he canceled it \Nbecause of the ships.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:27.39,01:10:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,How many cars \Ndoes your family have?
Dialogue: 0,01:10:30.73,01:10:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom's boyfriend \Nhas a Porsche.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:33.85,01:10:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Our parents are divorced too.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:35.81,01:10:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but there's nothing \Nwe can do about that.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:38.36,01:10:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Found a hat.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:40.32,01:10:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She has a thing for hats.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:42.36,01:10:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just like that at her age.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:44.86,01:10:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They made me feel safe.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:47.78,01:10:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So how did you meet Dr. Silberman?
Dialogue: 0,01:10:52.04,01:10:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, \Nnot the same way you did.
Dialogue: 0,01:10:56.08,01:11:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,My boyfriend asked me \Nto get them done.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:00.21,01:11:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not your husband?
Dialogue: 0,01:11:01.63,01:11:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no. We are not married. \NAnd probably never will.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:13.85,01:11:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,For the boys.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:20.23,01:11:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,They seem to like each other, huh?
Dialogue: 0,01:11:22.53,01:11:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,She is adorable.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:24.57,01:11:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:27.91,01:11:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So tell me, Mr. Karpov, \Nhow much did you pay?
Dialogue: 0,01:11:31.58,01:11:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,One billion euro. Per seat.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:37.08,01:11:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,- That's disgusting. \N- Oh, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,01:11:40.71,01:11:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Curtis, \NI wasn't always businessman.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:44.63,01:11:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I am a boxer.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:47.01,01:11:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Was my only playing \Nwhen I was boy back in Murmansk.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:50.85,01:11:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And my coach, \Nhis name was also Yuri.
Dialogue: 0,01:11:55.39,01:11:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He always said:
Dialogue: 0,01:11:57.60,01:12:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,"If someone wants to beat you, \Nhe has to kill you first. "
Dialogue: 0,01:12:06.95,01:12:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very nice.
Dialogue: 0,01:12:08.70,01:12:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,01:12:10.12,01:12:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But tell me, what would you have done \Nif you rich like me?
Dialogue: 0,01:12:15.87,01:12:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Look. \NThey are wonderful children, huh?
Dialogue: 0,01:12:21.09,01:12:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, guys.
Dialogue: 0,01:12:22.67,01:12:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The plan is to refuel in Hawaii, \Nso sit down and buckle up.
Dialogue: 0,01:12:26.26,01:12:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Gordon and I will do the rwst.
Dialogue: 0,01:12:31.14,01:12:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,01:12:34.47,01:12:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Go get the guys.
Dialogue: 0,01:12:39.35,01:12:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Guys, there's a... \NYou might wanna...
Dialogue: 0,01:13:00.83,01:13:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,01:13:02.29,01:13:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The state of Hawaii.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:05.55,01:13:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Not good. That is not good.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:14.51,01:13:16.27,Default,,0,0,0,,How much fuel do we have left?
Dialogue: 0,01:13:16.43,01:13:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Not enough. We're going to \Nhave to make a water landing...
Dialogue: 0,01:13:19.85,01:13:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,...somewherw in South China Sea.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:22.02,01:13:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Great. At least we're not gonna need \Nthe landing gear.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:24.77,01:13:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,- What about it? \N- Oh, we lost it all. in Vegas.
Dialogue: 0,01:13:50.22,01:13:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello. I'm sorry. Who is this?
Dialogue: 0,01:13:53.59,01:13:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Yoko Delgatto. \NDo you wanna speak to my daddy?
Dialogue: 0,01:14:00.89,01:14:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, please.
Dialogue: 0,01:14:02.56,01:14:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Who should I say is calling?
Dialogue: 0,01:14:08.15,01:14:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell him it's his father.
Dialogue: 0,01:14:11.11,01:14:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You're my grandpa?
Dialogue: 0,01:14:14.07,01:14:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sweetheart, I am.
Dialogue: 0,01:14:18.29,01:14:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy, Daddy, \NGrandpa's on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,01:15:24.39,01:15:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. President, sir.
Dialogue: 0,01:15:29.44,01:15:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. President.
Dialogue: 0,01:15:33.49,01:15:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,- What's the matter, sweetie? \N- She can't find her daddy.
Dialogue: 0,01:15:38.95,01:15:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you two \Nget comfy on that couch?
Dialogue: 0,01:15:41.08,01:15:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Sally, come help them out, okay?
Dialogue: 0,01:15:45.16,01:15:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll find your daddy.
Dialogue: 0,01:15:54.92,01:15:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Who can help me \Nwith missing persons?
Dialogue: 0,01:15:56.76,01:15:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, man. \NI'm really busy right now.
Dialogue: 0,01:16:00.51,01:16:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean... Of course, sir. \NSorry, Mr. President.
Dialogue: 0,01:16:03.60,01:16:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about it. \NYou're doing a great job, son.
Dialogue: 0,01:16:32.63,01:16:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,- What? \N- The capital's been hit by a 9.4.
Dialogue: 0,01:16:35.13,01:16:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We've lost communication.
Dialogue: 0,01:16:36.63,01:16:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,- Where's it centered? \N- North Chesapeake Bay.
Dialogue: 0,01:16:43.39,01:16:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Anheuser, the Russian president's \Non the line, sir.
Dialogue: 0,01:16:47.23,01:16:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,01:16:49.19,01:16:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We just entered Chinese airspace.
Dialogue: 0,01:16:52.94,01:16:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's affirmative, Mr. President.
Dialogue: 0,01:16:54.98,01:16:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Until communication is restored, \NI suppose I am in command.
Dialogue: 0,01:17:00.66,01:17:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it appears that all other \Nheads of state are en route...
Dialogue: 0,01:17:03.41,01:17:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,...with the exception \Nof the Italian prime minister...
Dialogue: 0,01:17:06.45,01:17:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,...who has also decided \Nto stay behind and trust in prayer.
Dialogue: 0,01:18:18.28,01:18:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The Earth's crust has begun to shift, \NDr. Helmsley.
Dialogue: 0,01:18:20.78,01:18:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- By what degree? \N-1.2 degrees, but it's still moving.
Dialogue: 0,01:18:24.16,01:18:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what happens next?
Dialogue: 0,01:18:25.62,01:18:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Once the movement \Nof our land masses comes to a halt...
Dialogue: 0,01:18:28.29,01:18:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see a simulation, Scotty.
Dialogue: 0,01:18:30.25,01:18:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,...expect the formation \Nof gigantic tsunamis...
Dialogue: 0,01:18:32.67,01:18:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,...proportional to the magnitude \Nof the corresponding quakes.
Dialogue: 0,01:18:53.60,01:18:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,From what we have just learned...
Dialogue: 0,01:18:54.40,01:18:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,...Tokyo seems to have taken \Nthe full force of the earthquake.
Dialogue: 0,01:18:58.52,01:19:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point, \Nunconfirmed reports indicate...
Dialogue: 0,01:19:00.94,01:19:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,...that large areas of land \Nare underwater.
Dialogue: 0,01:19:04.03,01:19:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Please stay tuned for further...
Dialogue: 0,01:19:15.92,01:19:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Tony...
Dialogue: 0,01:19:18.13,01:19:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I called.
Dialogue: 0,01:19:23.30,01:19:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I was too late.
Dialogue: 0,01:19:29.51,01:19:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they got out in time.
Dialogue: 0,01:19:32.98,01:19:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You never know. They...
Dialogue: 0,01:20:03.26,01:20:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Harry!
Dialogue: 0,01:21:02.23,01:21:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm coming home, Dorothy.
Dialogue: 0,01:21:31.30,01:21:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything?
Dialogue: 0,01:21:34.18,01:21:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing. Just static. \NNot even an emergency signal.
Dialogue: 0,01:21:51.07,01:21:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't think about \Nwhat's going on down there.
Dialogue: 0,01:22:00.58,01:22:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember that old Beetle \Nwe used to camp in?
Dialogue: 0,01:22:02.75,01:22:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We could never get the roof up.
Dialogue: 0,01:22:04.79,01:22:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,01:22:06.55,01:22:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We definitely traded up.
Dialogue: 0,01:22:11.43,01:22:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Tried to find our old spot \Nat Yellowstone...
Dialogue: 0,01:22:13.84,01:22:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,...when I went camping \Nwith the kids...
Dialogue: 0,01:22:17.01,01:22:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,...but I couldn't find it.
Dialogue: 0,01:22:31.07,01:22:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All global ground communication \Nhas ceased, sir.
Dialogue: 0,01:22:37.12,01:22:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The only signals our satellites \Nare picking up...
Dialogue: 0,01:22:40.54,01:22:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,...are coming from the vessels \Nin Cho Ming.
Dialogue: 0,01:22:43.62,01:22:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there's a piece of good news.
Dialogue: 0,01:22:45.83,01:22:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Any updates, doctor?
Dialogue: 0,01:22:47.25,01:22:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We expect the tsunamis \Nto reach landfall in every continent.
Dialogue: 0,01:22:50.59,01:22:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The Cho Ming area will be impacted \Nin approximately six hours.
Dialogue: 0,01:22:55.84,01:22:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,it looks like the crust has shifted \Nby almost 23 degrees...
Dialogue: 0,01:22:59.06,01:23:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,...to the southwest.
Dialogue: 0,01:23:01.06,01:23:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The data also shows the Earth's poles \Nhave reversed their magnetic fields.
Dialogue: 0,01:23:06.11,01:23:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,These are their new positions.
Dialogue: 0,01:23:08.44,01:23:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're...
Dialogue: 0,01:23:10.73,01:23:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You're telling me \Nthat the North Pole...
Dialogue: 0,01:23:13.70,01:23:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,...is now somewhere in Wisconsin?
Dialogue: 0,01:23:16.12,01:23:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, that's the South Pole now.
Dialogue: 0,01:23:27.21,01:23:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Engine failure. \NTwo of the six are down.
Dialogue: 0,01:23:29.67,01:23:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We must get ready.
Dialogue: 0,01:23:32.67,01:23:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- How long do we have? \N- Fifteen minutes. Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,01:23:38.05,01:23:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,- Better wake up the kids. \N- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,01:24:11.75,01:24:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is it time?
Dialogue: 0,01:24:16.55,01:24:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,- Dad, what's wrong? \N- Well, Sasha said we gotta land...
Dialogue: 0,01:24:19.55,01:24:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,...and it's gonna be a little bumpy \Nand maybe a little wet.
Dialogue: 0,01:24:23.43,01:24:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy?
Dialogue: 0,01:24:30.86,01:24:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold her steady.
Dialogue: 0,01:24:50.17,01:24:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy, \NI'm not a really good swimmer.
Dialogue: 0,01:24:51.71,01:24:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, no, that's all right. \NThat's what you got this for. Right?
Dialogue: 0,01:24:56.88,01:24:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like being in a swimming pool, \Nonly it's got more cool stuff.
Dialogue: 0,01:25:00.14,01:25:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, it's got a whistle, \Nand a light thing. Right?
Dialogue: 0,01:25:03.56,01:25:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought we were going to China.
Dialogue: 0,01:25:06.68,01:25:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we gotta land here.
Dialogue: 0,01:25:11.77,01:25:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're just all gonna \Nstay together, right?
Dialogue: 0,01:25:14.19,01:25:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- No, we're not, we're gonna die. \N- No. We're not.
Dialogue: 0,01:25:17.86,01:25:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Promise?
Dialogue: 0,01:25:19.49,01:25:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I promise you \Nwe're gonna all stay together...
Dialogue: 0,01:25:21.74,01:25:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,...no matter what happens, okay?
Dialogue: 0,01:25:38.55,01:25:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Jackson.
Dialogue: 0,01:25:40.55,01:25:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuri.
Dialogue: 0,01:25:43.05,01:25:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you better come up here.
Dialogue: 0,01:25:45.56,01:25:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna go check this out.
Dialogue: 0,01:25:47.18,01:25:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,- Dad. Where are you going? \N- I'll be back.
Dialogue: 0,01:25:49.35,01:25:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,- You said you'd stay with us. \N- We gotta buckle up. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,01:25:53.56,01:25:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, don't ask me \Nhow that happened...
Dialogue: 0,01:25:55.94,01:25:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,...but there is no more ocean...
Dialogue: 0,01:25:57.57,01:25:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,...and we're close \Nto where we wanted to go.
Dialogue: 0,01:25:59.78,01:26:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like the world shifted \Nby 1000 miles.
Dialogue: 0,01:26:02.16,01:26:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,One thousand five hundrwd \Nand seventy-eight to be exact.
Dialogue: 0,01:26:04.91,01:26:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,it's called \NEarth Crust Displacement Theory.
Dialogue: 0,01:26:07.49,01:26:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor Hapgood, 1958.
Dialogue: 0,01:26:10.46,01:26:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Way to go, Charlie.
Dialogue: 0,01:26:15.59,01:26:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,01:26:17.92,01:26:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We just lost our last two engines.
Dialogue: 0,01:26:38.90,01:26:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna shoot for that glacier. \Nit's gonna get rocky.
Dialogue: 0,01:26:42.20,01:26:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, this is gonna sound crazy, \Nbut here's what you have to do.
Dialogue: 0,01:26:50.08,01:26:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Unbuckle. \NCome on, come on, come on.
Dialogue: 0,01:26:53.79,01:26:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuri! What are we doing?
Dialogue: 0,01:26:55.83,01:26:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We are taking the Bentley.
Dialogue: 0,01:26:59.92,01:27:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Not yet. Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,01:27:02.63,01:27:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,it has to be perfect.
Dialogue: 0,01:27:04.34,01:27:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost there.
Dialogue: 0,01:27:06.09,01:27:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,- Come on. \N- Get in the car.
Dialogue: 0,01:27:18.65,01:27:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, go. Now. Pull.
Dialogue: 0,01:27:26.32,01:27:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no!
Dialogue: 0,01:27:31.83,01:27:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Go. Go, Jackson.
Dialogue: 0,01:27:33.41,01:27:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No, we gotta wait \Nfor Sasha and Gordon.
Dialogue: 0,01:27:36.08,01:27:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Go. Make sure everybody gets out \Nof the plane before I touch down.
Dialogue: 0,01:27:39.88,01:27:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,01:27:41.09,01:27:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be fine. \NI have to touch this baby down.
Dialogue: 0,01:27:45.68,01:27:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,01:28:02.03,01:28:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There he is. I see him.
Dialogue: 0,01:28:02.65,01:28:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,- Wherw is Sasha? Wherw is Sasha? \N- Come on. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,01:28:06.32,01:28:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He said he's fine. We should get \Nout of here before he touches down.
Dialogue: 0,01:28:09.62,01:28:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no. Don't go. \NWe have to wait for him.
Dialogue: 0,01:28:12.33,01:28:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Go, Jackson. Go.
Dialogue: 0,01:28:14.41,01:28:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,- Don't go! \N- it won't start. it won't start.
Dialogue: 0,01:28:18.25,01:28:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Just shut up, everybody!
Dialogue: 0,01:28:21.84,01:28:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,...start.
Dialogue: 0,01:28:26.30,01:28:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Voice control. Sold me on it.
Dialogue: 0,01:30:08.53,01:30:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,01:30:32.09,01:30:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to \Nthe People's Republic of China.
Dialogue: 0,01:30:34.89,01:30:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Good to be here. Say hi, kids.
Dialogue: 0,01:30:37.22,01:30:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hi. \N- Hi.
Dialogue: 0,01:30:38.47,01:30:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What color are your passes?
Dialogue: 0,01:30:41.77,01:30:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What color \Nare your boarding passes?
Dialogue: 0,01:30:46.02,01:30:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I have green card.
Dialogue: 0,01:30:48.40,01:30:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,For my boys and me.
Dialogue: 0,01:30:50.44,01:30:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,01:30:55.37,01:30:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuri. Yuri.
Dialogue: 0,01:30:57.70,01:31:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuri, it's a mistake. A joke, right?
Dialogue: 0,01:31:01.25,01:31:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,01:31:03.08,01:31:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You think I didn't know \Nabout you and Sasha?
Dialogue: 0,01:31:08.21,01:31:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,May God bless \Nthat poor bastard's soul.
Dialogue: 0,01:31:16.89,01:31:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, guys. Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,01:31:21.14,01:31:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, boys.
Dialogue: 0,01:31:24.52,01:31:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,- Does anybody have any money? \N- I do, I do.
Dialogue: 0,01:31:26.73,01:31:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You got a billion euros?
Dialogue: 0,01:31:33.20,01:31:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Wilson?
Dialogue: 0,01:31:35.16,01:31:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Captain Michaels, \Nskipper of the American ship.
Dialogue: 0,01:31:37.91,01:31:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Please accept my condolences \Nfor your father.
Dialogue: 0,01:31:40.33,01:31:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, captain.
Dialogue: 0,01:31:43.46,01:31:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Anheuser, \Nyour party is the last to arrive.
Dialogue: 0,01:31:50.46,01:31:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There've been reports \Nof severe damage, captain.
Dialogue: 0,01:31:52.96,01:31:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the status of Ark Number 3?
Dialogue: 0,01:31:55.01,01:31:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We haven't done \Na complete assessment yet...
Dialogue: 0,01:31:57.51,01:31:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,...but it looks like we lost it.
Dialogue: 0,01:32:54.03,01:32:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave it to the Chinese.
Dialogue: 0,01:32:56.03,01:32:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't think it was possible.
Dialogue: 0,01:32:58.03,01:32:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Not in the time we had.
Dialogue: 0,01:33:00.28,01:33:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's Ark Number 3, sir.
Dialogue: 0,01:33:02.66,01:33:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The roof collapsed on it \Nduring the shifting of the Earth's crust.
Dialogue: 0,01:33:06.87,01:33:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ.
Dialogue: 0,01:33:09.58,01:33:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Boarding of Ark Number 3 will be \Ndelayed due to technical difficulties.
Dialogue: 0,01:33:13.21,01:33:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,- Excuse me. \N- We paid a fortune!
Dialogue: 0,01:33:14.88,01:33:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Please be patient \Nas we keep you updated.
Dialogue: 0,01:33:19.09,01:33:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What he said about you and Sasha, \Nis it true?
Dialogue: 0,01:33:21.43,01:33:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Sasha was worth \N100 times a man like Yuri.
Dialogue: 0,01:33:25.18,01:33:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have listened to you, \NDr. Silberman.
Dialogue: 0,01:33:27.93,01:33:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I actually liked the way I looked \Nbefore that monster talked me into it.
Dialogue: 0,01:33:33.57,01:33:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You hear that?
Dialogue: 0,01:33:37.90,01:33:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Over there !
Dialogue: 0,01:33:41.32,01:33:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hey! \N- Hey!
Dialogue: 0,01:33:43.03,01:33:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,- Stop! Stop! Please! \N- Hey! Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,01:33:49.25,01:33:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,01:33:51.50,01:33:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop! Stop! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,01:33:55.55,01:33:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Help!
Dialogue: 0,01:34:06.51,01:34:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,01:35:00.15,01:35:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Satnam, where are you?
Dialogue: 0,01:35:01.65,01:35:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,- On the Nampan Plateau. \N- What?
Dialogue: 0,01:35:05.66,01:35:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a tidal wave \Ncoming from the east.
Dialogue: 0,01:35:07.28,01:35:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,- it's gigantic. \N- Satnam, what happened?
Dialogue: 0,01:35:11.50,01:35:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We never got picked up, Adrian.
Dialogue: 0,01:35:13.79,01:35:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The airlift never came.
Dialogue: 0,01:35:17.50,01:35:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,01:35:19.88,01:35:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Satnam.
Dialogue: 0,01:35:45.74,01:35:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,- The flooding is coming this way? \N- Mary. Where are we set up?
Dialogue: 0,01:35:48.83,01:35:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Over therw.
Dialogue: 0,01:35:53.91,01:35:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Get me the satellite images \Nfrom Nampan, India.
Dialogue: 0,01:35:55.29,01:35:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,- Okay, right away. \N- What's happening?
Dialogue: 0,01:35:59.21,01:36:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Satnam was talking \Nabout another wave...
Dialogue: 0,01:36:02.01,01:36:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,...coming from the east.
Dialogue: 0,01:36:07.09,01:36:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,- Holy mother. \N- The flooding is gonna hit earlier?
Dialogue: 0,01:36:09.72,01:36:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is that what you're telling me? \NThe second wave is closer?
Dialogue: 0,01:36:12.60,01:36:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,- Plug in the new data. \N- Okay.
Dialogue: 0,01:36:16.48,01:36:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,When's it gonna get here? Talk to me, \NHelmsley. When's it gonna hit?
Dialogue: 0,01:36:19.81,01:36:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Adjust the countdown.
Dialogue: 0,01:36:37.62,01:36:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Twenty-eight minutes, \N10 seconds to impact.
Dialogue: 0,01:36:40.67,01:36:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,01:36:42.09,01:36:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, I need to speak to the other \Nheads of state immediately.
Dialogue: 0,01:36:45.72,01:36:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,- Right away. Taylor? \N- Aye, captain. Standing by.
Dialogue: 0,01:36:48.68,01:36:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ark 6, stand by. Ark 7, stand by.
Dialogue: 0,01:36:51.43,01:36:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- Carl Anheuser, acting CIC, Ark 4. \N- Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,01:36:54.27,01:36:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Requesting emergency conference, \NT-99.
Dialogue: 0,01:37:32.89,01:37:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Attention: All construction workers, \Noff deck.
Dialogue: 0,01:37:36.14,01:37:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,All crew members, onboard now.
Dialogue: 0,01:37:39.19,01:37:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They're opening the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,01:37:41.40,01:37:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,They are leaving without us.
Dialogue: 0,01:37:44.32,01:37:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Step back. Get back. \NWhat did I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,01:37:47.78,01:37:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They are leaving you behind too. \NLook, idiot.
Dialogue: 0,01:37:50.86,01:37:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Please be patient.
Dialogue: 0,01:37:55.58,01:37:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,01:38:00.12,01:38:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Follow me.
Dialogue: 0,01:38:19.06,01:38:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,initiate security procedures.
Dialogue: 0,01:38:21.23,01:38:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Time to impact: \N17 minutes, 42 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,01:38:35.91,01:38:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Green lights on pressure, \NMr. Anton?
Dialogue: 0,01:38:37.99,01:38:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Green lights across the board, \Ncaptain.
Dialogue: 0,01:38:51.80,01:38:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do they have anchors?
Dialogue: 0,01:38:53.34,01:38:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they're not spaceships, \Nbuddy. They're arks.
Dialogue: 0,01:38:56.80,01:38:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,01:39:43.39,01:39:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop.
Dialogue: 0,01:39:44.60,01:39:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,01:39:47.65,01:39:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,01:39:55.28,01:39:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Engage the support mechanisms.
Dialogue: 0,01:39:56.95,01:39:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Aye, aye, captain. \NEngaging bow-anchor supports.
Dialogue: 0,01:39:59.33,01:40:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,How long are these things expecting \Nto hold us in place?
Dialogue: 0,01:40:02.29,01:40:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They're just meant to withstand \Nthe first impact of the waves.
Dialogue: 0,01:40:31.82,01:40:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Caesar.
Dialogue: 0,01:40:53.88,01:40:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Good boy.
Dialogue: 0,01:40:55.80,01:40:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to Mommy. Caesar!
Dialogue: 0,01:40:59.26,01:41:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, where's Tamara?
Dialogue: 0,01:41:03.43,01:41:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy look!
Dialogue: 0,01:41:06.10,01:41:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on. Caesar, come on.
Dialogue: 0,01:41:08.35,01:41:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,- Tamara! \N- I'm coming.
Dialogue: 0,01:41:18.03,01:41:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Take him.
Dialogue: 0,01:41:50.14,01:41:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The people of Russia...
Dialogue: 0,01:41:53.73,01:41:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,...along with China...
Dialogue: 0,01:41:57.15,01:42:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,...and Japan, agree.
Dialogue: 0,01:42:01.20,01:42:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Open the gates.
Dialogue: 0,01:42:05.16,01:42:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The United Kingdom, \NSpain, France, Canada, Germany...
Dialogue: 0,01:42:09.37,01:42:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,...and I believe I may also speak \Nfor the Italian prime minister...
Dialogue: 0,01:42:14.00,01:42:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,...we vote to let these people \Ncome in.
Dialogue: 0,01:42:22.84,01:42:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain Michaels.
Dialogue: 0,01:42:26.06,01:42:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,01:42:31.14,01:42:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the captain.
Dialogue: 0,01:42:32.85,01:42:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in a few moments, \Nwe will open the gates...
Dialogue: 0,01:42:35.61,01:42:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,...and get you people in.
Dialogue: 0,01:42:37.57,01:42:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Please step back \Nand clear the platform.
Dialogue: 0,01:42:43.57,01:42:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,P- yew, it stinks.
Dialogue: 0,01:43:04.84,01:43:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,- They are opening the gates. \N- Go. Go.
Dialogue: 0,01:43:07.39,01:43:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Climb! Don't look down! Climb! Go!
Dialogue: 0,01:43:15.56,01:43:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with the gate?
Dialogue: 0,01:43:17.06,01:43:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like it didn't run the full cycle. \NWe're checking, captain.
Dialogue: 0,01:43:20.78,01:43:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold it.
Dialogue: 0,01:43:22.86,01:43:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold it, people.
Dialogue: 0,01:43:28.49,01:43:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Four minutes to impact.
Dialogue: 0,01:44:14.96,01:44:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to the lower deck. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,01:44:16.67,01:44:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,- We are loaded, captain. \N- Well, then let's lock it up. Now.
Dialogue: 0,01:44:35.64,01:44:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, \NCho Ming Airfield's been hit.
Dialogue: 0,01:44:39.40,01:44:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Put me on emergency com, \NMr. Taylor.
Dialogue: 0,01:44:41.32,01:44:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Aye. You're on, captain.
Dialogue: 0,01:44:43.82,01:44:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the captain speaking.
Dialogue: 0,01:44:46.32,01:44:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We expect to be impacted \Nby water shortly.
Dialogue: 0,01:45:02.46,01:45:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All stations, prepare for impact.
Dialogue: 0,01:45:44.92,01:45:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Collision pressure \Njust below 80 pascal, captain.
Dialogue: 0,01:45:47.34,01:45:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,0.2 mil surface compression \Non bow sensors, captain.
Dialogue: 0,01:45:50.01,01:45:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,track Dr. Helmsley
Dialogue: 0,01:45:53.18,01:45:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor...
Dialogue: 0,01:45:55.06,01:45:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,...it's Air Force One.
Dialogue: 0,01:46:14.49,01:46:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,- The mid-ship anchor is hit. \N- We're destabilizing.
Dialogue: 0,01:46:17.16,01:46:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The bow anchor's giving in.
Dialogue: 0,01:46:53.66,01:46:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,impact warning.
Dialogue: 0,01:46:55.37,01:46:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Thirty degrees west.
Dialogue: 0,01:46:57.41,01:46:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Forty-five degrees east.
Dialogue: 0,01:46:59.33,01:47:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Target elevation, 29,035 feet.
Dialogue: 0,01:47:02.29,01:47:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We're headed straight \Nfor the north face...
Dialogue: 0,01:47:04.71,01:47:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,...of Mount Everest, Mr. Anheuser.
Dialogue: 0,01:47:07.04,01:47:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we can't start our engines, \Nwe will not survive the impact.
Dialogue: 0,01:47:20.81,01:47:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Distance to impact: 1850 meters.
Dialogue: 0,01:47:37.24,01:47:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Distance to impact: 400 meters.
Dialogue: 0,01:47:40.29,01:47:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Underwater ridge ahead. \NWe're going to run aground, captain.
Dialogue: 0,01:47:46.75,01:47:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,- Sir, the gate is sealed. \N- That's affirmative, captain.
Dialogue: 0,01:47:49.50,01:47:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Anton, start the engine.
Dialogue: 0,01:47:51.55,01:47:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Aye, aye, captain. Full reverse.
Dialogue: 0,01:48:02.22,01:48:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,- Too fast! We're not gonna make it. \N- Distance to impact: 50 meters.
Dialogue: 0,01:48:07.10,01:48:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Forty meters.
Dialogue: 0,01:48:32.05,01:48:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Reverse motion activated.
Dialogue: 0,01:48:34.34,01:48:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Distance to impact: 10 meters.
Dialogue: 0,01:48:38.43,01:48:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Twenty meters.
Dialogue: 0,01:48:48.19,01:48:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,01:48:54.40,01:48:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hard to port. \N- Aye, captain. Hard to port.
Dialogue: 0,01:49:25.64,01:49:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The end. "
Dialogue: 0,01:49:25.68,01:49:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen, \Nthis is Captain Michaels speaking.
Dialogue: 0,01:49:28.89,01:49:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in a few minutes I will give orders \Nto unseal the decks.
Dialogue: 0,01:49:32.19,01:49:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,- Come on. \N- At 2345 last night...
Dialogue: 0,01:49:34.61,01:49:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,...our sister arks, Numbers 6 and 7, \Nhave joined our course.
Dialogue: 0,01:49:40.32,01:49:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,For the first time on ourjourney...
Dialogue: 0,01:49:42.16,01:49:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,...we'll have clear skies \Nand moderate-to-good air quality.
Dialogue: 0,01:49:45.33,01:49:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,As you know, our passenger count \Nis way over capacity.
Dialogue: 0,01:49:48.79,01:49:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So please be careful \Nwhen you step out.
Dialogue: 0,01:49:51.42,01:49:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, enjoy the fresh air.
Dialogue: 0,01:49:57.21,01:49:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I hold him?
Dialogue: 0,01:49:59.05,01:50:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. He can be your dog too, \Nif you like.
Dialogue: 0,01:50:01.84,01:50:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,01:50:07.10,01:50:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,- Where have you been all my life? \N- Gift shop.
Dialogue: 0,01:51:07.33,01:51:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Adrian, excellent.
Dialogue: 0,01:51:10.16,01:51:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I called because we just got \Nour first satellite feed.
Dialogue: 0,01:51:13.08,01:51:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The equalization \Nof the oceanic seabeds...
Dialogue: 0,01:51:15.75,01:51:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,...has not turned out \Nto be as extreme as we expected.
Dialogue: 0,01:51:18.42,01:51:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The waters are receding much faster \Nthan we thought, thank God.
Dialogue: 0,01:51:22.26,01:51:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is hard to believe...
Dialogue: 0,01:51:24.22,01:51:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,...but the Himalayas \Nare no longer the roof of the world.
Dialogue: 0,01:51:27.43,01:51:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,it's now the Drakensberg mountains \Nof KwaZulu-Natal.
Dialogue: 0,01:51:30.85,01:51:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire African continent \Nhas risen.
Dialogue: 0,01:51:33.10,01:51:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Several thousand feet, \Nand it likely never even flooded.
Dialogue: 0,01:51:36.23,01:51:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why they call it \Nthe Cape of Good Hope.
Dialogue: 0,01:51:38.77,01:51:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We've already set course for it.
Dialogue: 0,01:51:47.74,01:51:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Daddy, \Nwhen will we go back home?
Dialogue: 0,01:51:50.49,01:51:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we talked about that.
Dialogue: 0,01:51:51.95,01:51:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We're gonna find a new home \Nout here somewhere, right?
Dialogue: 0,01:51:55.79,01:51:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, wherever we're all together, \Nthat's home.
Dialogue: 0,01:51:58.71,01:52:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Right? Don't be scared.
Dialogue: 0,01:52:01.17,01:52:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,01:52:04.59,01:52:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No more Pull-Ups.
Dialogue: 0,01:52:09.47,01:52:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice.
